  "title": "Infant Educator| West",
  "description": "<p>Job Description:  </p><ul><li>Consistently maintaining regular observation and evaluation of child’s development and progress</li><li>Ensure safety of each child through close supervision, whether in the classroom, play area, or any other areas in the school compound</li><li>Conduct childcare routines in a manner that is prompt, hygienic and consistent with early child development practices. These routines include diapering, feeding, bathing, hand washing, napping and transitioning between activities</li><li>Assist to maintain daily journal of milk feeds, solid feeds, diapering etc, in accordance to relevance for each age group.</li></ul><p><strong>Requirements:</strong></p><ul><li>Certificate in Infant/Toddler Care and Development (CIT) / Higher Certificate in Infant Care (HCIC) / Advanced Certificate in Early Years (ACEY)</li><li>Ability to build good rapport with parents and various stakeholders</li></ul>",
